<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1656,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,284,1656,1682]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Etymology</emphasis>
.The generic name is a combination derived from 
<taxonomicName box="[864,1020,1657,1682]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[864,1020,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Leptodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1076,1133,1657,1682]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">pilos</emphasis>
, a cap in Greek, a marked diagnostic sclerite on the female 
<taxonomicName box="[537,657,1695,1721]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Epigynum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">epigynum</taxonomicName>
, characteristic of the new genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1656,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1733,1759]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Small gnaphosids with colouration, body shape and general eye configuration as in 
<taxonomicName box="[151,314,1772,1797]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,314,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Leptodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. AME, the largest eyes, are borne on a common black patch. Male without dorsal scutum. Chelicerae with small conventional teeth, unlike the peculiar, angular teeth of 
<taxonomicName box="[1092,1251,1811,1836]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1092,1251,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Leptodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Labium wider than long. Palpus of male apically armed with closely grouped, often pointed laminae and a single-lobed tibial retrolateral apophysis. Female 
<taxonomicName box="[514,631,1888,1914]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Epigynum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="7" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">epigynum</taxonomicName>
with a median cavity and a broad, prominent cap-like anterior hood unlike the scape of 
<taxonomicName box="[379,535,1927,1952]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[379,535,1927,1952]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Leptodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1656,2030]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,152,448]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="9" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,333,1965,1991]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Comments</emphasis>
. The former genus 
<taxonomicName box="[567,723,1966,1991]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[567,723,1966,1991]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Leptodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recently divided by having the cheliceral dentition into two groups (
<bibRefCitation author="Murphy" box="[350,524,2004,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="49" refString="Murphy, J. A. (2007) Gnaphosid genera of the world. British Arachnological Society, St Neots, Cambs, 2 Volumes, 1 - 605." type="journal article" year="2007">
Murphy, 
<number box="[460,524,2004,2030]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2007.0">2007</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[543,699,2004,2029]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[543,699,2004,2029]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Leptodrassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes those species which like the type-species 
<taxonomicName box="[1300,1436,2004,2029]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="femineus">
<emphasis box="[1300,1436,2004,2029]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">L. femineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have two large angular retromarginal teeth, while the recently described genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Murphy" authorityName="Murphy" box="[1081,1339,152,178]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1081,1237,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Leptodrassex</emphasis>
Murphy
</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. simoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as type-species, possesses small, discrete conventional teeth. However, among the latter, a definite group of species is distinguished by their genital characters, namely a peculiar cap-like sclerite on the female 
<taxonomicName box="[151,271,268,294]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Epigynum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="8" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">epigynum</taxonomicName>
, and closely grouped laminae on the male palpus, unlike 
<taxonomicName box="[949,1059,268,293]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptodrassex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simoni">
<emphasis box="[949,1059,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. simoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Levy" box="[1076,1370,268,294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" refString="Levy, G. (1999 b) Spiders of six uncommon drassodine genera (Araneae: Gnaphosidae) from Israel. Israel Journal of Zoology, 45, 427 - 452." type="journal article" year="1999" yearSuffix="b">
Levy, 
<number box="[1151,1212,268,294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1999.0">1999</number>
b, figs 
<number box="[1292,1370,268,294]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="36.0" valueMax="37.0" valueMin="35.0">35–37</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The females within 
<taxonomicName box="[334,458,306,331]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[334,458,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Leptopilos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily separated from each other by the different shapes of the epigynal hood. Apart from the type-species 
<taxonomicName authority="Walckenaer, 1805" authorityName="Walckenaer" authorityYear="1805" box="[508,676,345,370]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Drassus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenerrimus">
<emphasis box="[508,676,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. tenerrimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the following species are here placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[1192,1323,345,370]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1192,1323,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Leptopilos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Dalmas, 1919" authorityName="Dalmas" authorityYear="1919" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pupa">
<emphasis box="[1341,1436,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. pupa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dalmas" box="[151,313,384,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="48" refString="Dalmas, R. de. (1919) Catalogue des araignees du genre Leptodrassus (Gnaphosidae), d'apres les materiaux de la collection E. Simon au Museum d'histoire naturelle. Bulletin du Museum d'histoire naturelle, Paris, (4), 1919, 243 - 250." type="journal article" year="1919">
Dalmas, 
<number box="[254,313,384,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1919.0">1919</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(not 
<bibRefCitation author="Chatzaki" box="[374,630,384,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="48" refString="Chatzaki, M., Thaler, K. &amp; Mylonas, M. (2002 a) Ground spiders (Gnaphosidae; Araneae) of Crete (Greece). Taxonomy and distribution I. Revue Suisse Zoology, 109 (3), 559 - 601." type="journal article" year="2002" yearSuffix="a">
Chatzaki et al., 
<number box="[555,617,384,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2002.0">2002</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chatzaki" box="[634,649,384,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="48" refString="Chatzaki, M., Thaler, K. &amp; Mylonas, M. (2002 b) Ground spiders (Gnaphosidae; Araneae) of Crete and adjacent areas of Greece. Taxonomy and distribution II. Revue Suisse de Zoology, 109 (3), 603 - 633." type="journal article" year="2002" yearSuffix="b">b</bibRefCitation>
= 
<taxonomicName box="[678,830,384,409]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levantinus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[678,830,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. levantinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[836,899,384,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Chatzaki, 2002" authorityName="Chatzaki" authorityYear="2002" box="[922,1294,384,410]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hadjissaranti">
<emphasis box="[922,1106,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. hadjissaranti</emphasis>
Chatzaki, 
<number box="[1232,1294,384,410]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chatzaki, 2002" authorityName="Chatzaki" authorityYear="2002" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manolisi">
<emphasis box="[1305,1436,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. manolisi</emphasis>
Chatzaki, 
<number box="[269,331,422,448]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[343,494,423,448]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levantinus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[343,494,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. levantinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[501,564,422,448]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[621,737,423,448]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Leptopilos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lakhish" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[621,737,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. lakhish</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[744,807,422,448]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
